article.headline: Pacific 79, CS Northridge 51
article.story: STOCKTON, Calif. (AP) -- Mike Webb made eight 3-pointers for a career-high 24 points to lead Pacific in its 79-51 victory over Cal State Northridge on Wednesday. Webb made seven 3-pointers in the first half as the Tigers improved to 19-7 and remained atop the Big West Conference at 9-2. Pacific won for the eighth time in nine games. The two-time defending Big West regular-season champion, Pacific never saw its lead fall below 21 points after beginning the second half with a 10-0 run. Webb left the game because of a thigh injury with 13:23 remaining and did not return despite coming within one 3-pointer of the school record for most in a game. Johnny Gray scored 18 points and had three 3-pointers for the Tigers, who made a season-high 14 3-pointers. Christian Maraker, the Big West's leading scorer and rebounder, had a game-high 10 rebounds to pace Pacific's 36-25 rebounding edge. Mike Efevberha scored 14 points to lead Cal State Northridge (10-14, 3-8), which didn't have another player with more than seven points. Pacific made 59.6 percent of its shots from the field, and 3-pointers by Steffan Johnson and Gray gave the Tigers a 68-38 advantage with 10:25 remaining. A 3-pointer by Wolfgang Raffety gave Pacific its biggest lead at 79-47 in the final minute. Webb's 3-pointers accounted for the Tigers' first two baskets and three of their first four, while his fourth trey gave Pacific a 20-10 lead 12 minutes into the game. He then had three consecutive 3-pointers in a 15-0 Pacific run that extended the Tigers' advantage to 35-12 four minutes later. The Tigers had four 23-point leads in the first half and a 41-22 edge at the break.
